feed.title: Brisbane Ranges National Park - Plants
feed.subtitle: A collection of vascular plants found within the Brisbane Ranges National Park and adjoining Steiglitz Historic Park. Any observations found within the boundaries of the reserve can be included. For observations on adjoining private land within the broader Brisbane Ranges landscape, there is another collection called "Brisbane Ranges surrounds - Plants". If you find a species in the national park or historic reserve that is not currently part of this collection, please notify me for inclusion - chris.lindorff@bigpond.com. Thanks.

entry.title: Melianthus comosus
entry.content: Very hardy weed that has colonised along the edges of the Sutherland's Creek south of Steiglitz. Infestations of multiple patches along creek, from 5 to 100s of plants. Photos taken by Jo Day.

entry.title: Pterostylis aciculiformis
entry.content: Although this plant is just outside the boundaries of the National Park, they are also found within the park. This plant appeared spontaneously this year - I have not seen it before in this location. Note the second photo for close-up of the labellum.

entry.title: Caladenia fuscata
entry.content: White coloured C fuscata (Dusky Fingers). ID'd on the basis of features such as the forward-pointing triangular extensions on mid-lobes, lack of yellow on lip/tip of labellum, glands on back of dorsal sepal and underneath sepals and petals. However noted a lack of prominent red transverse stripes on and underneath the labellum. Other C. fuscata nearby displayed the stripes extending further up the lobes and underneath the labellum. Just a variation perhaps in this plant? 4 pics.

entry.title: Grevillea micrantha
entry.content: The Brisbane Ranges form has leaves with granules confined to the veins on upper surface and broader grooves on undersurface. Found mainly in western and central Victoria. The climate is hot dry summers, cold wet winters, rainfall around 500mm annually.
